==Old High German==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic ''*ik'', possibly from a preform ''*ekaⁿ'' from Proto-Indo-European ''*{{IPAchar|eǵHóm}}'', or directly from ''*{{IPAchar|éǵoH}}''. Near cognates include Old English ''[[ic]]'', Old Saxon ''[[ik]]'', Old Norse ''[[ek]]'', Gothic [[𐌹𐌺]]
